  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 149</em>, <em>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 469</em></p><p><strong>Aura</strong> strong necromancy and transmutation <strong>CL</strong> 18th</p><p><strong>Slot</strong> weapon quality; <strong>Price</strong> +5 bonus; <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\"><strong>Description</strong></h3>This potent and feared ability allows the weapon to sever the heads of those it strikes. Upon a roll of natural 20 (followed by a successful roll to confirm the critical hit), the weapon severs the opponent's head (if it has one) from its body. Some creatures, such as many aberrations and all oozes, have no heads. Others, such as golems and undead creatures other than vampires, are not affected by the loss of their heads. Most other creatures, however, die when their heads are cut off. A <em>vorpal </em>weapon must be a slashing melee weapon. If you roll this special ability randomly for an inappropriate weapon, reroll.</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3><strong>Requirements</strong> Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>circle of death</em>, <em>keen edge</em>; <strong>Price</strong> -</p>",
